15 minute* fast ferry to Sydney CBD

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive sales agents are pleased to present to you, Lots 21 & 22, 22 Darley Road, Manly.

The corner office suite comprised of two lots with an internal area of 175sqm* plus three secure car spaces.  Situated within the premier office strata building for Manly, the office suite situated on level three enjoys elevated views of water over Cabbage Tree Bay and views of Manly's Eastern Hill.

The suite provides a modern open planned fit-out, three partitioned meeting rooms and excellent natural light. The facilities include lift access, ducted air-conditioning, common toilets and an internal kitchenette. 

The property benefits from the following key attributes: 

- Two adjoining lots amalgamated into one office suite
- Total internal area of 175sqm* plus three secure car spaces
- Net passing income of $108,129 per annum* on a flexible lease
- Ideal for both investors and owner occupiers
- Situated within the premier office strata building in Manly
- Premium location just metres from Manly Corso, Beach and Wharf
- 15 minute* fast ferry to Sydney CBD

Lots 21 & 22, 22 Darley Road will be sold via public auction on Tuesday, 10 December 2019 at 10.30am

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 10 Victoria Parade, Manly. This three storey freehold apartment block commands one of the best locations in Sydney’s Northern Beaches,just metres from the Manly Beach, Ferry Wharf and Corso. Consisting of 17 residential apartments, property presents a premier trophy investment with significant upside. 

10 Victoria Parade capitalises on the following key attributes: 

- Freehold apartment block comprising 17 residential units to be sold in one line
- First time offered to market in over 60 years
- Land area: 635sqm*
- Gross floor area: 809sqm*
- Gross passing income: $523,927 per annum*
- Secure investment with strata potential (S.T.C.A)
- R3 Medium Density Residential zoning
- Exclusive location & level walk to Manly Wharf, Beach & Corso
- North facing with substantial natural light
- Coveted suburb with strong performing property market and low vacancy

*Approximate

10 Victoria Parade, Manly will be sold via public auction on Tuesday, 23 October 2018 at 10.30am.

For more information or to request the information memorandum, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

CBRE as the exclusive selling agent, is pleased to present Suite 1, 18 Sydney Road, Manly. The property is a premium office suite comprising a large open plan office with a floor area of 353sqm* and six (6) secure car spaces. Situated on the doorstep of Manly’s pedestrian arcade on Sydney Road, the office suite provides a modern high-end practical fitout, sleek kitchenette and employee break out area, two generous enclosed offices or meeting rooms, male and female amenities, and an inviting reception area.

Suite 1, 18 Sydney Road is ideal for an owner occupier looking to operate from the space and take advantage of the extraordinary lifestyle that Manly has to offer including proximity to popular bars, cafés, restaurants, shops and Manly Beach, whilst being only a 20* minute ferry ride to Sydney’s CBD. Additionally, the property provides an outstanding investment opportunity that can capitalise off Manly’s high demand leasing market.

Suite 1, 18 Sydney Road, Manly capitalises on the following key attributes:

-Large 353sqm* of prime office suite
-Presented with an extremely rare six (6) secure car spaces in the centre of Manly 
-Offered with vacant possession, ideal for owner occupiers 
-On the doorstep of Manly’s popular pedestrian arcade ‘The Corso’
-Metres from the world-renowned Manly Beach, voted Australia’ best beach in TripAdvisor 2019 Travellers’ Choice Awards
-Lifestyle focussed locality in proximity to vibrant cafés, bars, restaurants, and retail.  
-Fantastic accessibility only moments from Manly Wharf with direct services to Sydney CBD
- A modern high-end practical fitout, sleek kitchenette and employee break out area, two generous enclosed offices or meeting rooms, male and female amenities, and an inviting reception area.
-Ideal for both owner occupiers and investors 

Suite 1, 18 Sydney Road, Manly will be sold via an online Public Auction on Tuesday 28th of September 2021 at 10.30am at AuctionWORKS (live stream & online bidding available).

Inspections to be held by appointment as per COVID-19 Greater Sydney restriction requirements. Please enquire directly with the exclusive agents to arrange a private viewing.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approx.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: PREMIUM OFFICE SUITE IN THE HEART OF MANLY

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as exclusive selling agents, under instructions from trustees, is pleased to present Shops 1-7, 25-27 South Steyne, Manly to be sold in-one-line. Situated on one of the most prominent corners of Manly, this trophy strata asset comprises five tenancies over seven lots. The property is currently fully leased, with International tenants Ben and Jerry’s occupying the corner position. Other tenancies in the offering include Manly Fish Market, Manly Fish Café, Blind Barrel and Ezymart. Accordingly, the property presents a prime opportunity for investors to attain a secure investment that benefits from high foot traffic and tourist exposure. This exciting investment opportunity offers a net lettable area of 433sqm* directly next to the council carpark, which experiences high amounts of foot and vehicular traffic. 

Shops 1-7, 25-27 South Steyne benefits from the following key attributes:
- 433sqm* of prime retail net lettable area
- Fully leased to 5 tenants, including international tenant Ben and Jerry's and national tenant Ezymart 
- High exposure corner position opposite Manly Beach
- Situated on one of the busiest pedestrian intersections in Manly

Shops 1-7, 25-27 South Steyne, Manly will be sold via Public Auction on Tuesday, 9th of March 2021 at AuctionWORKS (live stream & online bidding available).

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Arguably the best & last beachfront site

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive sales agent is pleased to present 61 North Steyne, Manly. Commanding an enviable position directly opposite Manly Beach, 61 North Steyne is arguably the best and  last Manly beachfront development site. 61 North Steyne offers discerning purchasers the opportunity to redevelop 411sqm* of prime Manly beachfront (STCA). The property’s R3 Medium Density Residential zoning, FSR 1.5:1 and 13m Height Limit, creates an exciting opportunity for a luxury residential development (STCA). With positioning directly along the beachfront, 61 North Steyne boasts pristine uninterrupted views along Manly Beach across the Pacific Ocean out to the horizon.

The North-East facing corner site has significant street frontage to North Steyne and Denison Street, bathing it in natural light whilst allowing seamless access for construction. 61 North Steyne offers exceptional convenience, just moments from popular dining options, The Corso, direct ferry services to Sydney CBD and bus services to Sydney CBD, North Sydney and greater Northern Beaches.


This property benefits from the following key attributes:

- Arguably the best and last development site along Manly Beachfront
- Premier North-East facing 411sqm* corner site
- Two significant frontages bathing the site in natural light whilst providing seamless access for construction
- Directly opposite Manly Beach
- Strong demand for luxury beachfront apartments from local affluent downsizers
- R3 Medium Density Residential zoning, 1.5:1 FSR and 13m Height Limit permitting with consent a luxury residential development
- Great accessibility moments to bus and ferry services to Sydney CBD, North Sydney, and greater Northern Beaches

Expressions of Interest closing Wednesday, 25 August 2021 at 4pm.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.
